Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The abductors of a Deeper Life Bible Church Pastor, Otamayomi Ogedengbe in Ondo State have made contact with his family. The kidnappers were said to have demanded the payment of N30 million ransom before the pastor who was kidnapped three days ago would be set free. Pastor Ogedengbe, a native of Akungba Akoko in Akoko South West Local Government Area of the state was kidnapped from a church located along Irese road in Akure South Local Government Area of the state on Monday night around 8:37pm. A family source said the kidnappers insisted that the ransom was not negotiable. With the details of the discussion with the family still sketchy as at press time, the victim’s wife, Yinka Ogedengbe cried out to security agencies to help rescue her husband unhurt as quickly as possible due to his state of health. Narrating the incident to the police, the pastor’s wife said her husband was abducted at the end of the church service by the armed men. A pastor, Rev. Genesis Zaka; three female church members; and two gatemen of Kauna Baptist Church, Danazunmi, near Grigori in Rafi Local Government Area of Niger State have been kidnapped by bandits.Findings have it that the names of the kidnapped female church members are Tabitha Luka, Liatu Nuhu and Rahila… In "Metro" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post)  -  Kidnappers of  the chairman of the All Progressives Congress in Akoko-Edo Local Government Area of Edo State,  Henry Ashofor, have reportedly demanded a N20 million ransom.   Ashofor was kidnapped last Saturday near Aiyetoro along the Igarra- Ibillo road on his way from… In "Top Stories" By Aderemi Bamgbose Odigbo (Ondo State) - The abductors of Olori Regina Akinrinmade, the wife of Oba Rufus Akinrinmade, the Orunja of Odigbo kingdom and her two daughters, have demanded N60 million ransom for their release. Chief Olu Akinsawe, the Odofin of Odigbo kingdom  confirmed this development to journalists on… In "News"